library(readxl)
library(tseries)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'quantmod':
##   method            from
##   as.zoo.data.frame zoo
filename = "C:/Users/j/Documents/Uni/ComSci 760/Weather Project/Data/BeachDataNoOutliers.xlsx"
sheetnames = excel_sheets(path = filename)


for (i in 1:length(sheetnames)) {

  # open the data from the sheet specified
  BeachData = read_xlsx(filename, sheet = sheetnames[i])
  
  # coerce to a irregulary sapced time series
  Ent_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Entero)
  Rain24_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain24)
  Rain48_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain48)
  Rain72_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain72)
  RainWA_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$RainWA)
  Solarhours_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Solarhours)

  # get the plot window to 3 rows by 2
  par(mfrow=c(3,2))

  # plot all the variables as time series
  barplot(Ent_ts$value, main=paste(sheetnames[i]," Ecoli"))
  barplot(Rain24_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 24 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Rain48_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 48 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Rain72_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 72 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(RainWA_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Accumulated 72 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Solarhours_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Solar hours"))

  # set the plot window back to 1,1
  par(mfrow=c(1,1))
  acf(Ent_ts$value, main=paste(sheetnames[i]," Ecoli"),na.action = na.pass)
  acf(Rain24_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 24 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Rain48_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 48 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Rain72_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 72 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(RainWA_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Accumulated 72 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Solarhours_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Solar hours"))
}

Same analysis but for years 2011 onwards

library(readxl)
library(tseries)


filename = "C:/Users/j/Documents/Uni/ComSci 760/Weather Project/Data/BeachDataNoOutliers.xlsx"
sheetnames = excel_sheets(path = filename)


for (i in 1:length(sheetnames)) {

  # open the data from the sheet specified
  BeachData = read_xlsx(filename, sheet = sheetnames[i])
  
  # get the data for just years 2011 onwards
  BeachData = BeachData[which(format(BeachData$DATE,'%Y') >= 2011),]
  
  # coerce to a irregulary sapced time series
  Ent_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Entero)
  Rain24_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain24)
  Rain48_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain48)
  Rain72_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Rain72)
  RainWA_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$RainWA)
  Solarhours_ts = irts(BeachData$DATE,BeachData$Solarhours)

  # get the plot window to 3 rows by 2
  par(mfrow=c(3,2))

  # plot all the variables as time series
  barplot(Ent_ts$value, main=paste(sheetnames[i]," Ecoli"))
  barplot(Rain24_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 24 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Rain48_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 48 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Rain72_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 72 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(RainWA_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Accumulated 72 Hour rainfall"))
  barplot(Solarhours_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Solar hours"))

  # set the plot window back to 1,1
  par(mfrow=c(1,1))
  acf(Ent_ts$value, main=paste(sheetnames[i]," Ecoli"),na.action = na.pass)
  acf(Rain24_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 24 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Rain48_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 48 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Rain72_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Prev 72 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(RainWA_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Accumulated 72 Hour rainfall"))
  acf(Solarhours_ts$value, main = paste(sheetnames[i], " Solar hours"))
}
